<sn class="col-12 col-md-10 ignore p-3 p-lg-5"><md>## Types of Fractions{.text-end}

| **Type of Fraction**      | **Definition**                                         | **Example**                             | **Relation (N &amp; D)** | **Result Meaning**     |
|---------------------------|--------------------------------------------------------|------------------------------------------|-----------------------|-------------------------|
| **Zero Fraction**         | Numerator is **0**, denominator is non-zero.           | $\frac{0}{5},\ \frac{0}{734}$            | $N = 0$               | Result = **0**          |
| **Proper Fraction**       | Numerator is **less than** denominator.                | $\frac{3}{5},\ \frac{2}{7}$              | $N &lt; D$               | Result **&lt; 1**          |
| **Improper Fraction**     | Numerator is **greater than or equal to** denominator. | $\frac{7}{4},\ \frac{8}{3}$              | $N &gt; D$ or $N = D$    | Result **≥ 1**          |
