</md></sn><sn><md>### Simplest form of Fraction


$$
\frac{A}{B} = \frac{A+n}{B+n} = \frac{A-n}{B-n} = \frac{A \times n}{B \times n} = \frac{\frac{A}{n}}{\frac{B}{n}} = \text{same ratio}
$$


Fractions are not always in their simplest form.Simplify involves ==removing all common factors (HCF)== from the numerator and denominator.Which reduce both into a simpler one


$\frac{A}{B}$ fraction if A and B has not ==Common factor==  then it is in already the simplest form.

If not then the Simplest form of a fraction $\frac{A}{B}$ is 

$$
\text{simplest form of } \frac{A}{B} = \frac{\frac{A}{F}}{\frac{B}{F}}
$$

where `F` is the HCF(A,B)

### Simplify the fraction $\frac{30}{50}$

`F` = HCF(30,50)


So `F` = 10


$$
\text{simplest form of } \frac{A}{B} = \frac{\frac{A}{F}}{\frac{B}{F}}
$$
$$
= \frac{\frac{30}{10}}{\frac{50}{10}}
$$
$$
 = \frac{3}{5}
$$






